<br>
Mobs that proc AE slows that are hard to resist.<br>
Mobs that proc any high damage AE or single target effect especially a lifetap.<br>
Mobs with very high dps but low hp.<br>
Mobs with high ac.<br>
<br>
and it gives people a desire to have wizards. Make them unsnareable to prevent quadding. Must run at sow speed or faster to make swarm kiting more difficult. And mobs cannot be low enough in level for DC to work and charms should be difficult to land.<br>
<br>
Unmezzable mobs are good too with low hp and being force to pull more than one at a time. <p>[60 Sorcerer] <a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=69194">Zuratuli</a> (Gnome) <<a href="http://www.insublimity.com">Sublimity</a>></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#000000><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub140.ezboard.com/bgraffeswizardcompilation.showUserPublicProfile?gid=fizziisotope>Fizzi Isotope</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Forum Wizard</span><br>  Posts: 54<br> <font color=#ffffff>(11/21/02 5:44 pm)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: There are two schools of thought.....</span><hr size=1> ... and put absurdly high exp modifiers or insanely desirable melee loot on the loot tables, otherwise groups will never, ever go there. <p></p><i>Edited by: <A HREF=http://pub140.ezboard.com/bgraffeswizardcompilation.showUserPublicProfile?gid=fizziisotope>Fizzi Isotope</A> at: 11/21/02 5:44:40 pm<br></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#33333><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub140.ezboard.com/bgraffeswizardcompilation.showUserPublicProfile?gid=garrathmoore>Garrath Moore</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Forum Evoker</span><br>  Posts: 422<br> <font color=#ffffff>(11/21/02 9:31 pm)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Yep</span><hr size=1> Groups will never go there unless there is a good damn reason to go there.  What will wind up happening is you will see it become CS, TD etc...Quadding wizards taking up residence where groups do not want to go, or have difficulty getting to quickly.<br>
